HEADWORD: Paralgesia
<hw>Par`al*ge"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.;
<ets>para-</ets> + Gr. <grk>'a`lghsis</grk> sense of pain.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Disordered sensibility to pain, including absence
of sensibility to pain, excessive sensibility to pain, and abnormal
painful results of stimuli.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Par`al*ge"sic</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

